$ Access SQL: update table from another table

In → development/databases/Access, records in a table can be updated from records in another table with the following syntax:
code {
update 
   dest_table dest inner join
   src_table  src             on src.id_dest = dest.id
 set
   dest.… = src.…
   dest.… = src.…
code }

This is demonstrated with the following copy/paste → development/languages/VBA[Visual Basic for Application] example:
gh|about-Access|/SQL/update-from-another-table.bas||

sa:
  → development/databases/Access/SQL[Access SQL]
